OL,3,CLasers 'powered by sunlight' could
OL,4,Ctransform space travel, scientists say
OL,6,FThe aim is to repurpose the light-
OL,7,Fharvesting antennae from certain types
OL,8,Fof photosynthetic bacteria to
OL,9,F"amplify" energy from sunlight, and
OL,10,Fconvert it into laser beams that can
OL,11,Ftransmit that energy across space.
OL,13,FThe scientists also hope that using
OL,14,Forganic materials rather than
OL,15,F"perishable" artificial components
OL,16,Fmeans the lasers could be effectively
OL,17,Fre-grown in space ` meaning they could
OL,18,Fbe kept in operation without new parts
OL,19,Fhaving to be sent up from Earth.
